The paper proposes an extension of the t-SNE method for visualizing high-dimensional data using f-divergences. This work is relevant to the fields of machine learning, artificial intelligence, computer vision, and information theory, which are covered by the arXiv sub-categories cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.CV, cs.SI, and cs.IT. Among these, cs.LG (Machine Learning) is the most likely category as the paper deals with a method for visualizing high-dimensional data, which is a common problem in machine learning. The other categories are also relevant as they deal with related topics such as computer vision and information theory.
